From linux-rg Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: linux-rg maintainers <linux-rg@local>
Date: Thu, 18 Jun 2026 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 13/13] sched/fair: lower default migration_cost (Cachy/Kolivas-adjacent)

CachyOS desktop policy uses 300000 ns vs mainline 500000. BORE already
disables tunable scaling; this sysctl tweak is the remaining low-risk
fair-class latency knob compatible with BORE and detach_tasks.

---
 kernel/sched/fair.c | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/kernel/sched/fair.c b/kernel/sched/fair.c
--- a/kernel/sched/fair.c
+++ b/kernel/sched/fair.c
@@ -96,7 +96,7 @@ static unsigned int normalized_sysctl_sched_base_slice	= 700000ULL;
 #endif /* CONFIG_SCHED_BORE */
 
-__read_mostly unsigned int sysctl_sched_migration_cost	= 500000UL;
+__read_mostly unsigned int sysctl_sched_migration_cost	= 300000UL;
 
 static int __init setup_sched_thermal_decay_shift(char *str)
 {
